The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning to train adaptive bit rate algorithms for video streaming, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the impact of congestion control algorithms on the performance of the trained algorithms, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and the simulation of network environments (cs.SY).
